<item>
            <title>[PDFBOX-1880] [PATCH] Type 1 Shading must not ignore current transformation matrix</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-1880</link>
                <project id="12310760" key="PDFBOX">PDFBox</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;My implementation for Type 1 Shading (&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-1869&quot; title=&quot;Implementation for ShadingType 1&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PDFBOX-1869&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PDFBOX-1869&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;) ignored the current transformation matrix, because I thought that the shading matrix would be relevant only. That is the cause for the wrong rendering of the rgbcube file. The attached patch fixes this.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12692903">PDFBOX-1880</key>
            <summary>[PATCH] Type 1 Shading must not ignore current transformation matrix</summary>
                <type id="1" iconUrl="https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/viewavatar?size=xsmall&amp;avatarId=21133&amp;avatarType=issuetype">Bug</type>
